  <scopecontent id="aspace_4739dd93b4a624f8af158f7a7953fa7e">
    <head>Scope and Content Notes</head>
<p>This collection contains the records of St. Peter's Episcopal Church, Oakland, Pittsburgh, Pa. It includes a historical sketch, parish registers, minutes of the Women's Guild, register of church services, deed to Burgwin pew, correspondence, newsclippings, and photographs. Series I includes a historical sketch of the church, 1850-1918. Sereis II includes Parish registers, 1852-1958. These registers contain baptisms, communicants, confirmations, marriages, burials, parishoners, families, church offerings, and rectors. Series III contains the minutes of the Women's Guild of St. Peter's, November, 1916 - October, 1928. Series IV contains a register of church services and the deed to pew number 50.</p><p>Series V includes miscellaneous correspondence concerning the relocation of the church and the designation of the church as a national historic landmark. Series VI includes newsclippings about the relocation of the church building, change of rectors, church social and educational activities, 85th anniversary, national landmark status, and architectural style. Series VII includes photographs of the church facade, Grant and Diamond streets before relocation; the church as it stands on Fifth and Craft Avenues; and photos of church groups and the church basketball team.</p>  </scopecontent>
